                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12857816" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 13:54:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the issue is unsynchronized access to the SoftValueSortedMap for each tableLocations in HConnectionManager - it can eventually get the treemap into a corrupt state where it infinite loops in the removal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857819" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:07:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In particular, HConnectionManager.locateRegionInMeta calls getCachedLocation outside of the regionLockObject. Although this appears to be &quot;read only&quot;, the SoftValueSortedMap calls through to treemap.remove and rq.poll, both of which are mutative.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible fixes: 1) add synchronization around getCachedLocation in HCM.locateRegionInMeta, or 2) Add synchronization internal to SoftValueSortedMap so that it becomes threadsafe.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;this appears to have been introduced by HBASE-2034&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857828" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:26:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;oops, I meant client, not RS here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857829" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:28:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, CHANGES.txt has the wrong number for the sync block change that caused this. It&apos;s really 2023&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857921" author="stack" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 18:22:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Change CHANGES.txt everywhere.  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m looking at changing the SVSM to internally use a ConcurrentSkipListMap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857923" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 18:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed it to synchronize all of its methods as a quick fix and it seemed to work OK so far (at least haven&apos;t run into it again yet)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857933" author="tlipcon" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 18:54:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the simple patch to just synchronize SoftValueSortedMap&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12858076" author="stack" created="Sat, 17 Apr 2010 02:20:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.  I thought the returns out of headmap and tailmap unsafe if iterated but Todd points out that head/tailmap makes copies so should be fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12858078" author="stack" created="Sat, 17 Apr 2010 02:35:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to the two branches and trunk.  Thanks for the patch Todd.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12860953" author="stack" created="Mon, 26 Apr 2010 15:26:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to add this to CHANGES.txt on 0.20_pre_durability.  I added it just now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12866912" author="stack" created="Wed, 12 May 2010 23:54:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking these as fixed against 0.21.0 rather than against 0.20.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017684" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:44:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
